Prerequisite

1. JDK 8.0
2. Gradle 
3. Eclipse
4. Apache Kafka

Download & install JDK - https://www.java.com/en/download/help/download_options.xml
Download & install Gradle - https://gradle.org/install/
Download & install Eclipse - http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/
Download & Install Apache Kafka - https://kafka.apache.org/downloads

Before run the application - Start the Kafka servers and create a new Topic "messenger" - https://kafka.apache.org/quickstart 

Create an executable JAR file by using the command - gradle clean build

After build successful, go to the build/libs directory, you will find the JAR file and run the JAR file by using the following command - java -jar spring-kafka-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar


